  <section id="meals">
    <h2>Daily Meal Plan</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Meal</th><th>Food Items & Timing</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Breakfast</td><td>After morning cardio: 3 eggs, 1 slice bread, cucumber, banana</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Snack 1</td><td>Mid-morning: Greek yogurt or protein shake + almonds or fruit</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Lunch</td><td>Pre-workout meal: Grilled chicken, rice or sweet potato, salad, olive oil</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Snack 2</td><td>After strength workout: Boiled egg or cheese + fruit</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Dinner</td><td>Final meal (if hungry): Grilled fish or eggs + vegetables + bread</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Optional Late Snack</td><td>Before bed: Herbal tea + boiled egg</td></tr>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="progression">
    <h2>Weekly Progression</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Week 1:</strong> Learn form, use light/moderate weights</li>
      <li><strong>Week 2:</strong> Slightly increase weights (2.5–5 kg)</li>
      <li><strong>Week 3:</strong> Increase reps or weights</li>
      <li><strong>Week 4:</strong> Increase weights or reduce rest time to 60 sec</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="weight">
